    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Boards, often carved in profile, that are components in chests or the support of stools or benches. Common support elements for stools in the Medieval period, and until the 17th century when legs became the norm.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011151/Fleming and Honour, Penguin Dictionary of the Decorative Arts (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079668/Green, Wood: Craft, Culture, History (2007)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bretter die oft im Profil bearbeitet sind, Komponenten an Truhen oder die Stützen von Stühlen oder Bänken. Übliche Stützelemente von Stühlen im Mittelalter und bis ins 17. Jahrhundert, als Beine gebräuchlich wurden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
